CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1951, pg. 7 reads: "Fashion Show At Kay Club - The Duchess Social Club gave a fashion show and popularity contest Sunday at the Kay Boy's Club. Miss Edith Kirby won the popularity title and Miss Ann Turner was her runner up.  Seated, left to right: Viola Spencer, vice president; Charlotte Smith, sponsor; Edith Kirby, social chairman and winner; Ann Turner, president, second winner, and Sylvia Smith.  Standing: Virginia Wright, Rachel Smith, secretary; Yvonne Green, Arlene Gieshen, Shirley Gilbert, Beverly Lewis, Geraldine Farrish, Marie Yates, Ida Yates, Barbara Morgan, Dolly Brown, Gloria Brice, Beatrice Glenn and Rosa Smith. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nineteen members of the Duchess Social Club, seated, left to right: Viola Spencer, Charlotte Smith, Edith Kirby, Most Popular winner; Ann Turner, and Sylvia Smith; standing: Virginia Wright, Rachel Smith, Yvonne Green, Arlene Gieshen, Shirley Gilbert, Beverly Lewis, Geraldine Farrish, Marie Yates, Ida Yates, Barbara Morgan, Dolly Brown, Gloria Brice, Beatrice Glenn, and Rosa Smith, gathered in Kay Boys' Club for fashion show and popularity contest, another version
